{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01GbZY27tgPiepBpfUDEb3ed","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→Feature: Stage Contracts\n     2→  Stage contracts define schema validation, semantic validation, and\n     3→  deterministic Markdown rendering for every stage in every built-in\n     4→  flow preset. Contract evaluation follows a fixed order: schema first,\n     5→  semantics second, rendering last. Failures at any step short-circuit\n     6→  subsequent steps.\n     7→\n     8→  @SC-EVAL-001\n     9→  Scenario: Successful planning contract evaluation\n    10→    Given a planning stage contract\n    11→    When a valid planning payload is submitted\n    12→    Then schema validation passes\n    13→    And semantic validation passes\n    14→    And a deterministic Markdown artifact is produced\n    15→    And the result carries no outcome failure\n    16→\n    17→  @SC-EVAL-002\n    18→  Scenario: Successful execution contract evaluation\n    19→    Given an execution stage contract\n    20→    When a valid execution payload is submitted\n    21→    Then schema validation passes\n    22→    And semantic validation passes\n    23→    And a deterministic Markdown artifact is produced\n    24→    And the result carries no outcome failure\n    25→\n    26→  @SC-EVAL-003\n    27→  Scenario: Successful validation contract evaluation with passing outcome\n    28→    Given a validation stage contract\n    29→    When a valid validation payload with outcome \"approved\" is submitted\n    30→    Then schema validation passes\n    31→    And semantic validation passes\n    32→    And a deterministic Markdown artifact is produced\n    33→    And the result carries no outcome failure\n    34→\n    35→  @SC-EVAL-004\n    36→  Scenario: Schema validation failure prevents semantic validation\n    37→    Given a planning stage contract\n    38→    When an invalid JSON payload missing required fields is submitted\n    39→    Then schema validation fails with failure class \"schema_validation_failure\"\n    40→    And semantic validation does not run\n    41→    And rendering does not run\n    42→    And no success bundle is returned\n    43→\n    44→  @SC-EVAL-005\n    45→  Scenario: Domain validation failure prevents rendering\n    46→    Given an execution stage contract\n    47→    When a schema-valid payload with empty change_summary and no steps is submitted\n    48→    Then schema validation passes\n    49→    And semantic validation fails with failure class \"domain_validation_failure\"\n    50→    And rendering does not run\n    51→    And no success bundle is returned\n    52→\n    53→  @SC-EVAL-006\n    54→  Scenario: QA/review outcome failure with valid payload\n    55→    Given a validation stage contract\n    56→    When a valid validation payload with outcome \"rejected\" is submitted\n    57→    Then schema validation passes\n    58→    And semantic validation passes\n    59→    And a deterministic Markdown artifact is produced\n    60→    And the result carries outcome failure class \"qa_review_outcome_failure\"\n    61→    And the validated bundle is still returned\n    62→\n    63→  @SC-EVAL-007\n    64→  Scenario: Every stage in every built-in flow has contract coverage\n    65→    Given the set of all built-in flow presets\n    66→    Then every stage in every preset resolves to exactly one contract\n    67→    And no stage is left without a contract\n    68→\n    69→  @SC-EVAL-008\n    70→  Scenario: Deterministic rendering produces identical output\n    71→    Given a validated planning payload\n    72→    When the payload is rendered twice\n    73→    Then both renders are byte-identical\n    74→\n    75→  @SC-EVAL-009\n    76→  Scenario: Non-passing review outcomes are not treated as schema or domain failures\n    77→    Given a validation stage contract\n    78→    When a valid validation payload with outcome \"request_changes\" is submitted\n    79→    Then schema validation passes\n    80→    And semantic validation passes\n    81→    And the failure class is \"qa_review_outcome_failure\"\n    82→    And the failure class is not \"schema_validation_failure\"\n    83→    And the failure class is not \"domain_validation_failure\"\n    84→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a43e306d-d21a-484c-9b37-70212164e32a","uuid":"fc955427-1b22-427b-ab85-e7a29bbc41c6","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/conformance/features/stage_contracts.feature","content":"Feature: Stage Contracts\n  Stage contracts define schema validation, semantic validation, and\n  deterministic Markdown rendering for every stage in every built-in\n  flow preset. Contract evaluation follows a fixed order: schema first,\n  semantics second, rendering last. Failures at any step short-circuit\n  subsequent steps.\n\n  @SC-EVAL-001\n  Scenario: Successful planning contract evaluation\n    Given a planning stage contract\n    When a valid planning payload is submitted\n    Then schema validation passes\n    And semantic validation passes\n    And a deterministic Markdown artifact is produced\n    And the result carries no outcome failure\n\n  @SC-EVAL-002\n  Scenario: Successful execution contract evaluation\n    Given an execution stage contract\n    When a valid execution payload is submitted\n    Then schema validation passes\n    And semantic validation passes\n    And a deterministic Markdown artifact is produced\n    And the result carries no outcome failure\n\n  @SC-EVAL-003\n  Scenario: Successful validation contract evaluation with passing outcome\n    Given a validation stage contract\n    When a valid validation payload with outcome \"approved\" is submitted\n    Then schema validation passes\n    And semantic validation passes\n    And a deterministic Markdown artifact is produced\n    And the result carries no outcome failure\n\n  @SC-EVAL-004\n  Scenario: Schema validation failure prevents semantic validation\n    Given a planning stage contract\n    When an invalid JSON payload missing required fields is submitted\n    Then schema validation fails with failure class \"schema_validation_failure\"\n    And semantic validation does not run\n    And rendering does not run\n    And no success bundle is returned\n\n  @SC-EVAL-005\n  Scenario: Domain validation failure prevents rendering\n    Given an execution stage contract\n    When a schema-valid payload with empty change_summary and no steps is submitted\n    Then schema validation passes\n    And semantic validation fails with failure class \"domain_validation_failure\"\n    And rendering does not run\n    And no success bundle is returned\n\n  @SC-EVAL-006\n  Scenario: QA/review outcome failure with valid payload\n    Given a validation stage contract\n    When a valid validation payload with outcome \"rejected\" is submitted\n    Then schema validation passes\n    And semantic validation passes\n    And a deterministic Markdown artifact is produced\n    And the result carries outcome failure class \"qa_review_outcome_failure\"\n    And the validated bundle is still returned\n\n  @SC-EVAL-007\n  Scenario: Every stage in every built-in flow has contract coverage\n    Given the set of all built-in flow presets\n    Then every stage in every preset resolves to exactly one contract\n    And no stage is left without a contract\n\n  @SC-EVAL-008\n  Scenario: Deterministic rendering produces identical output\n    Given a validated planning payload\n    When the payload is rendered twice\n    Then both renders are byte-identical\n\n  @SC-EVAL-009\n  Scenario: Non-passing review outcomes are not treated as schema or domain failures\n    Given a validation stage contract\n    When a valid validation payload with outcome \"request_changes\" is submitted\n    Then schema validation passes\n    And semantic validation passes\n    And the failure class is \"qa_review_outcome_failure\"\n    And the failure class is not \"schema_validation_failure\"\n    And the failure class is not \"domain_validation_failure\"\n","numLines":84,"startLine":1,"totalLines":84}}}
