{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_011bPFMwDwqqjfiSrhNHFNBe","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01PsxFq3GJWbiHEYDAeaBEEy","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/root/new-ralph-burning/.ralph/tmp/logs/20260311185357-impl-response-001.md","content":"# Implementation Response (Iteration 1)\n\n## Changes Made\n1. **QA/review outcome failure returns error, not success with side-band flag** (Required Change 1)\n   - Added `ContractError::QaReviewOutcome { stage_id, outcome }` variant to `shared/error.rs` that maps to `FailureClass::QaReviewOutcomeFailure`.\n   - Removed `EvalSuccess` wrapper from `contracts.rs`. `evaluate()` now returns `Result<ValidatedBundle, ContractError>` directly.\n   - Replaced `check_outcome_failure()` (which returned `Option<FailureClass>`) with `check_outcome()` (which returns `Result<(), ContractError>`). Non-passing QA/review outcomes now produce `Err(ContractError::QaReviewOutcome { .. })`.\n   - Outcome check runs after semantic validation but before rendering, so no artifact is produced on the error path — satisfying \"on any failure, no success bundle is returned.\"\n\n2. **Conformance expectations updated to encode error contract** (Required Change 2)\n   - Updated unit tests `non_passing_review_maps_to_qa_review_outcome_failure`, `conditionally_approved_maps_to_qa_review_outcome_failure`, and `sc_eval_006_qa_review_outcome_failure` to assert `unwrap_err()` with `ContractError::QaReviewOutcome` match and `FailureClass::QaReviewOutcomeFailure`.\n   - Added `sc_eval_009_non_passing_review_not_schema_or_domain_failure` test asserting the failure class is distinct from schema and domain failures.\n   - Updated Gherkin `stage_contracts.feature` SC-EVAL-006 to say \"the result is an error\" and \"no success bundle is returned\" and \"rendering does not run\".\n   - Updated Gherkin SC-EVAL-009 to assert error result with no success bundle.\n   - Removed all `outcome_failure` field references from success-path tests.\n\n3. **Runtime validation alignment with generated schema** (Recommended Improvement)\n   - Added `jsonschema = \"0.18\"` dev-dependency.\n   - Added `schema_validation_rejects_what_generated_schema_marks_required` test: compiles the generated JSON Schema via `jsonschema::JSONSchema`, validates a bad payload against it, and confirms runtime `evaluate()` rejects the same payload.\n   - Added `schema_validation_accepts_what_generated_schema_accepts` test: confirms both generated schema and runtime evaluation accept a valid payload.\n\n## Could Not Address\nNone\n\n## Pending Changes (Pre-Commit)\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/Cargo.toml` — added `jsonschema` dev-dependency\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/src/shared/error.rs` — added `QaReviewOutcome` variant, updated `failure_class()` and `stage_id()` match arms\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/workflow_composition/contracts.rs` — removed `EvalSuccess`, changed `evaluate()` return type, replaced `check_outcome_failure` with `check_outcome`\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/unit/stage_contract_test.rs` — updated 8 tests to assert error semantics, added 3 new tests (SC-EVAL-009, schema alignment x2)\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/conformance/features/stage_contracts.feature` — updated SC-EVAL-006 and SC-EVAL-009 scenarios\n- All 51 unit tests pass, `cargo clippy --all-targets --all-features -- -D warnings` is clean\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":123,"cache_read_input_tokens":66689,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":123},"output_tokens":25,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a43e306d-d21a-484c-9b37-70212164e32a","uuid":"3540c8d4-b869-406d-8f02-5f6c5873490e"}
